"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The method `ax.set_xticks` expects the tick positions to be in the form of numerical values or datetime objects, not strings. Additionally, `ax.set_xticklabels` should be used with caution as it can lead to misalignment of ticks and labels if not used correctly. Instead, `ax.xaxis.set_major_locator` and `ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter` should be sufficient for setting the ticks and their labels.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19\\n<ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n<ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n>fig.autofmt_xdate()\"\n}"